HEADWORD: Metallophone
<hw>Me*tal"lo*phone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>metallum</ets> metal + Gr. <?/ sound.]</ety> <fld>(Music)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>An instrument like a pianoforte, but having metal bars
instead of strings.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An instrument like the
xylophone, but having metallic instead of wooden bars.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

